<subSubSection id="C4AEBF9BFFE4FFA5FF34B179FE8CFDE8" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8C0BEC10FFE4FFA5FF34B179FE8CFDE8" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FF34B179FEFFFEC8" bold="true" box="[189,256,302,328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FE98B179FD92FEC8" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[273,621,302,328]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FE98B179FD92FEC8" box="[273,621,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Xenoastrosphaeriella aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FD66B178FC9DFEC8" box="[751,866,303,328]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tornata">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FD66B178FC9DFEC8" box="[751,866,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. tornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having similar shapes of ascostromata, asci and ascospores. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FE0FB104FDF6FEEC" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[390,521,339,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FE0FB104FDF6FEEC" box="[390,521,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FCCBB104FC4BFEEC" box="[834,948,339,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tornata">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FCCBB104FC4BFEEC" box="[834,948,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. tornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the ascospores color (dark olivaceous to brown vs. brown to reddish-brown), size (55–70 × 6–7 vs. 48–52 × 7–8 μm) and numbers of septa (3-septate vs. 5- septate). 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FF79B1CDFDB4FE34" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[240,587,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FF79B1CDFDB4FE34" box="[240,587,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Xenoastrosphaeriella aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FCB6B1CCFC4CFE34" box="[831,947,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trochus">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FCB6B1CCFC4CFE34" box="[831,947,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. trochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="148FF095FFE4FFA5FC4DB1CDFBBDFE34" box="[964,1090,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[176,1425,210,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,187,1198]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram generated from maximum likelihood analysis based on combined LSU, SSU and tef1-α sequence data. Bootstrap values for maximum likelihood (ML) equal to or greater than 75% and clade credibility values greater than 0.95 from Bayesian-inference analysis were labelled on the branches. The ex-type strains are in bold. The newly generated sequences are indicated in red." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6503896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6503896/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">FIGURE 1</figureCitation>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FAA1B1CCFA54FE34" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1320,1451,411,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FAA1B1CCFA54FE34" box="[1320,1451,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FF76B1E8FE8EFE58" box="[255,369,446,472]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trochus">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FF76B1E8FE8EFE58" box="[255,369,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. trochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having conical to mammiform, superficial, carbonaceous ascomata, cylindric-clavate asci and broadly fusiform ascospores, but differs from the latter in the ascospores color (dark olivaceous to brown vs. brown to reddish-brown) and dimension (55–70 × 6–7 vs. 45–55 × 4.5–6 μm). Moreover, the comparison of the 
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FB75B251FAC1FDA0" box="[1276,1342,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">tef1-α</emphasis>
sequence data between 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FEA8B27CFE5DFDC4" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[289,418,555,580]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FEA8B27CFE5DFDC4" box="[289,418,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FE51B27CFDB5FDC4" box="[472,586,554,580]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trochus">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FE51B27CFDB5FDC4" box="[472,586,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. trochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed 25 base pair differences, which also indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FB54B27CFAA2FDC4" authorityName="D. F. Bao, H. Y. Su &amp; Z. L. Luo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1245,1373,555,580]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquatica">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FB54B27CFAA2FDC4" box="[1245,1373,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4BB49793FFE4FFA5FA1AB27CFF24FDE8" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Astrosphaeriellaceae" genus="Xenoastrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trochus">
<emphasis id="BEC03002FFE4FFA5FA1AB27CFF24FDE8" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">X. trochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
